cs.CL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.FL, cs.DS 

This paper discusses a logical and grammatical formalism based on pomset logic, which is closely related to linear logic and coherence spaces. As such, it is likely to be classified under arXiv CS sub-categories that deal with formal logic, natural language processing, and computational linguistics. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as it deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper may also be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these categories deal with topics related to formal logic, automata theory, and computational linguistics.
